# 🚀 First-Year CSE AIML – Intermediate Level Roadmap 2026–2027
Very Simple English • Realistic & Very Detailed • Super Long Guide  
For First-Year Students Who Are Already Intermediate in Coding & Want Strong AI/ML Future

Hello bro!  
You are in first year B.Tech CSE / AIML (or AI & DS / similar branch) — but your level is already intermediate.  
That is really great. Most first-year students are still struggling with basic Python syntax, simple loops, or first console program.  
You already know Python quite well, have solved many DSA problems (maybe 200–500+), built some decent projects (console apps, simple scripts, maybe early ML), and used GitHub a little.  

This roadmap is specially made for students like you — not beginner level (too easy), not advanced level (too much pressure in first year).  
We keep everything balanced and realistic:  
- DSA medium focus (quality > huge numbers)  
- Real AI/ML projects that look good on resume  
- Easy deployment (Streamlit, Hugging Face)  
- Internship applications early  
- No 1000+ problems or 10-hour daily grind — we respect college, internals, exams, friends, sleep  

Small daily steps + consistency + balance = you will be strong intermediate (ready for good summer 2027 internships) by end of second year.

